The paper discusses generalization error bounds for stochastic gradient methods in non-convex learning problems, which are central topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, the paper focuses on Stochastic Gradient Langevin Dynamics (SGLD), which is a widely used stochastic optimization algorithm in deep learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the implications of the results for deep learning, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the impacts of stochastic gradient methods on generalization error, which is a topic in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
